    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "interfaces/wallet: replace raw receive-request string APIs with typed methods",
    "user": {
      "login": "itdeveloper1988",
      "id": 98523682,
      "node_id": "U_kgDOBd9aIg",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98523682?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/itdeveloper1988",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/itdeveloper1988/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Replace getAddressReceiveRequests() and setAddressReceiveRequest() with three typed methods on interfaces::Wallet:\r\n\r\n- getReceiveRequests()  -> vector<WalletReceiveRequest>\r\n- addReceiveRequest()   -> optional<int64_t> (assigned ID)\r\n- eraseReceiveRequest() -> bool\r\n\r\nThe previous interface passed serialized blobs between the wallet and GUI, forcing GUI code to handle serialization/deserialization of RecentRequestEntry objects directly. This created tight coupling to the wallet storage format and caused the GUI to crash on startup if it encountered a malformed entry.\r\n\r\nThe wallet layer now owns:\r\n- ID assignment (scans existing keys for max ID, assigns max+1)\r\n- Timestamp generation (calls GetTime() internally)\r\n- Serialization via Qt-independent mirror structs (RecipientData, RequestEntryData) that are byte-compatible with the existing DB format\r\n- Graceful error recovery: malformed entries are logged via LogWarning and skipped instead of crashing\r\n\r\nThe GUI (RecentRequestsTableModel) no longer contains any serialization logic. The SERIALIZE_METHODS macro, nVersion field, and nReceiveRequestsMaxId tracker are removed from RecentRequestEntry and the table model.\r\n\r\nA regression test is added that writes a malformed blob directly into the wallet address book and verifies getReceiveRequests() returns successfully without crashing.",
